  "market_context": "GBPUSD on December 27, 2023, entering the London Killzone. Price on the hourly chart had swept a prior low and displaced upward, forming a low-high-lower low-higher high sequence, then dropped down to a 5-minute structure for a refined entry.",
  "key_observation": "An hourly breaker block overlapping a fair value gap (unicorn model) coincided with London Killzone, and the same structure repeated fractally on the 5-minute chart with a sweep, displacement, breaker block and FVG entry zone.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly chart, identify the sweep of the prior low followed by displacement upward.",
    "Step 2: Mark the low-high-lower low-higher high sequence, identifying the up-close candles as a breaker block.",
    "Step 3: Note that the breaker block overlaps a fair value gap, forming a unicorn model on the hourly chart.",
    "Step 4: Confirm timing aligns with entering the London Killzone, then drop down to the 5-minute timeframe.",
    "Step 5: On the 5-minute chart, observe the same fractal pattern: low, high, lower low sweeping an important level, then displacement to a higher high.",
    "Step 6: Mark the 5-minute breaker block and the associated fair value gap as the refined entry zone.",
    "Step 7: Define entry at the start of the fair value gap, with stop placed below the 5-minute swing low.",
    "Step 8: Set first target at 2R or the prior highs, and project the manipulation leg to the -2 standard deviation level, yielding a 3.62R potential trade."
  ],
